Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting 
Network in Korean at 1300 GMT on 1 March reports on departures 
of foreign officials who were in Pyongyang. 
  Ho Chong-man, responsible vice chairman of the Central 
Standing Committee of the General Association of Koreans 
Residing in Japan, left Pyongyang on 1 March by plane after 
visiting the DPRK. Workers Party of Korea Central Committee 
Secretary Kim Yong-sun and other functionaries concerned bade 
him farewell at the airport. 
  Juan Jose Leon Vega, Cuban ambassador to the DPRK, returned 
home on 1 March by plane after being summoned from Cuba. 
  (Jean Carlos Elia Valori), general secretary of the Italian 
Institute for the Study of International Relations, returned 
home on 1 March by plane. 

